==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} ''έρημσς'' meaning alone, solitary, desolate; through Latin ''eremita''; through French ''eremite''; through Old English ''ermite / eremite''

===Noun===
'''eremite''', plural ''[[eremites]]'''

# A [[hermit]]; a religious recluse, someone who lives alone.

